Now, from linear-response theory~\cite{LeHur,Goldstein} and using an
exact identity 
for the Green funciton of the bosonic modes,
\begin{eqnarray}
G_{kk'}({\omega}) & \equiv & \big<a_k^\dagger({\omega}) a_{k'}^{\phantom{\dagger}}(-{\omega})\big>\nonumber \\
 &=& \frac{\delta_{kk'}}{{\omega}-{\omega}_k} + \frac{g_k g_{k'} \chi({\omega})}
{({\omega}-{\omega}_k)({\omega}-{\omega}_{k'})}
\end{eqnarray}
which relates the scattering matrix to the qubit response, one obtains the
reflection and transmission coefficients,
\begin{eqnarray}
\label{RKubo}
R({\omega}) & = & (2\pi \alpha {\omega})^2 |\chi({\omega})|^2\\
\label{TKubo}
T({\omega}) & = & (2\pi \alpha {\omega})^2 [\chi'({\omega})]^2+[1-2\pi\alpha{\omega}\chi''({\omega})]^2 ,
\end{eqnarray}
as well as the total inelastic deficit,

